(2180, '_transient_feed_0d102f2a1f4d6bc90eb8c6ffe18e56ed', 'a:4:{s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:3:\"rss\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"\n\n\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:7:\"version\";s:3:\"2.0\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:7:\"channel\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"The Events Calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"WordPress event plugins for awesome people\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:13:\"lastBuildDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 29 Aug 2024 15:07:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"language\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"en-US\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"item\";a:10:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"QR Code Mastery for Event Professionals\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:153:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/qr-code-for-ticket-validation/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 30 Aug 2024 17:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Event Management\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545689\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:572:\"<p>Remember the last time you watched a line of grumpy attendees snake around the block, waiting to get their tickets checked? Or that nagging worry about fake tickets slipping through the cracks? QR code ticket validation is here to banish those headaches for good. In fact, the number of consumers in the United States who&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/qr-code-for-ticket-validation/\">QR Code Mastery for Event Professionals</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Jaime Marchwinski\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24557:\"\n<p>Remember the last time you watched a line of grumpy attendees snake around the block, waiting to get their tickets checked? Or that nagging worry about fake tickets slipping through the cracks? QR code ticket validation is here to banish those headaches for good.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, the number of consumers in the United States who scan a QR code with their smartphone has nearly doubled in the last five years<strong>,</strong><a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/1337584/number-of-smartphone-qr-code-scanners-usa/\"><strong> </strong>reaching almost 100 million</a> (2019–2024).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, we’ll explore the world of QR codes and how they&#8217;re revolutionizing event entry. You&#8217;ll discover how this little square can speed up check-ins, tighten security, and make your events run like a well-oiled machine.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And the best part? We&#8217;ve got a secret weapon to share: <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets Plus</a>. It&#8217;s the tool that&#8217;ll make QR code validation a piece of cake for your events.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-why-qr-codes-are-vital-for-event-professionals\"><strong>Why QR codes are vital for event professionals</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>QR codes are indispensable tools for event pros like you. Here&#8217;s why:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Say goodbye to those snail-paced check-in lines.</strong> QR codes speed things up big time. Just a quick scan and your attendees are in. It&#8217;s real-time, it&#8217;s fast, and it keeps the line moving. In the U.S., <a href=\"https://ecommons.cornell.edu/server/api/core/bitstreams/d0dc3ab2-d891-47e3-b7f6-fd1c4da92d80/content\">folks start getting antsy after just five minutes in line</a>. With QR codes, you&#8217;ll keep those frowns turned upside down.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>QR codes are security superheroes.</strong> Remember those problems of fake tickets or sneaky gate-crashers? QR codes shut that down. Each ticket gets its own unique code. And if someone tries to use a fake or already-scanned ticket? The system flags it faster than you can say &#8220;busted&#8221;.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Your attendees will love how easy it is to use QR codes.</strong> No more fumbling with paper tickets or forgetting them at home. It&#8217;s all on their phones. Happy attendees mean <a href=\"https://ijarsct.co.in/Paper12313.pdf\">higher attendance rates and better vibes all around</a>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Here&#8217;s a bonus: <strong>QR codes are green. </strong>Yep, you heard that right. No more printing stacks of paper tickets that end up in the trash. It&#8217;s a small change that makes a <a href=\"https://www.theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/sustainable-event-tips/\">big difference for our planet</a>.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>So, whether you&#8217;re running a cozy local gig or a massive conference, QR codes have your back. They&#8217;re fast, secure, user-friendly, and eco-friendly — a winning combo in any event pro&#8217;s playbook.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-leveraging-event-tickets-plus-for-seamless-qr-code-integration\"><strong>Leveraging Event Tickets Plus for seamless QR code integration</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you&#8217;re sold on QR codes, let&#8217;s see how we can make them work for you. Enter <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets Plus</a>. This <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\">WordPress</a> plugin lets you <a href=\"https://www.theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/free-tools-to-help-you-sell-more-tickets/\">sell tickets online</a> and handle check-ins right from your website. It comes with built-in QR code magic, making your life as an event pro a whole lot easier. Let&#8217;s see how it works.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"353\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-665x353.jpg\" alt=\"Event Tickets by The Events Calendar\" class=\"wp-image-2544859\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-665x353.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-300x159.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-140x74.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-768x408.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1536x816.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-2048x1088.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-430x228.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-645x343.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-2000x1063.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1068x567.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-460x244.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1602x851.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1074x571.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-512x272.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1611x856.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-707x376.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-600x319.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-500x266.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-key-features-of-event-tickets-plus\"><strong>Key features of Event Tickets Plus</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets Plus is packed with features to make your QR code ticketing easy. Let&#8217;s break them down:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Automatic QR code generation: </strong>No need to fiddle with complicated software. Event Tickets Plus creates unique QR codes for each ticket purchase and <a href=\"https://www.theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/introducing-ticket-emails-a-no-code-solution-to-ticket-email-customization/\">emails them to your attendees</a>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Mobile app for check-in:</strong> Got a smartphone? You&#8217;re set. The <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.theeventscalendar.eventticketsplus&amp;hl=en_IN\">Event Tickets Plus app</a> (available for both Android and iOS) lets you <a href=\"https://www.theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/how-to-use-qr-ticket-check-in-on-the-event-tickets-plus-mobile-app/\">scan QR codes and check in attendees</a> in seconds.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Real-time attendance tracking:</strong> Watch your event fill up in real time. As tickets are scanned, you&#8217;ll see exactly who&#8217;s arrived and when.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Plays well with others:</strong> Event Tickets Plus fits right in with other WordPress plugins, like <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\">The Events Calendar</a>, giving you a one-stop shop for all your event management needs. Of course, it also works great on its own.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Customizable registration:</strong> Want to know your attendees&#8217; T-shirt sizes or meal preferences? You can ask for this info during ticket purchase.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>GDPR compliance: </strong>We take privacy seriously. Event Tickets Plus helps you keep attendee data safe and secure, in line with <a href=\"https://gdpr.eu/\">GDPR</a> rules. The Event Tickets Plus app, which is required to scan QR codes, does not store any user-related information and is GDPR compatible. </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Contributor accounts: </strong>Let your staff help with check-ins without giving them the keys to the kingdom. Set up special accounts that can scan tickets but can&#8217;t access sensitive backend info.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to get started? Check out our step-by-step guide on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/using-qr-codes-with-event-tickets-plus/\">using QR Codes with Event Tickets Plus</a>. It&#8217;ll walk you through the setup process, making sure you&#8217;re up and running in no time.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"296\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-665x296.jpg\" alt=\"Visual representation of QR code ticket validation with Event Tickets Plus\" class=\"wp-image-2545694\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-665x296.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-300x133.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-140x62.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-768x341.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-1536x683.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-2048x911.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-430x191.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-645x287.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-2000x889.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-1068x475.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-460x205.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-1602x712.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-1074x478.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-512x228.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-1611x716.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-707x314.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-600x267.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-graphic-500x222.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-scanning-devices-and-software\"><strong>Scanning devices and software</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Scanning QR codes for Event Tickets Plus is very easy:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Grab your smartphone or tablet. Any device with a camera will do. Next, download the free <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.theeventscalendar.eventticketsplus&amp;hl=en_IN\">Event Tickets Plus app</a>. You&#8217;ll find it on the <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/games?hl=en\">Google Play Store</a> for Android or the <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/in/app-store/\">App Store</a> for iOS.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>To connect the app to your site, you&#8217;ll use an API key or a QR code from your WordPress admin area. It&#8217;s quick and easy.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>If you need more options, you can use any QR code scanner app, like <a href=\"https://quickmark.com.tw/\">QuickMark</a>. Just make sure you&#8217;re logged into your website with the right permissions. This gives you flexibility if you need it.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>With these simple tools, you&#8217;ll be ready to start scanning tickets and welcoming attendees in no time.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-665x461.jpeg\" alt=\"Event Tickets Plus app\" class=\"wp-image-2545693\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-665x461.jpeg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-300x208.jpeg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-123x85.jpeg 123w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-768x532.jpeg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-430x298.jpeg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-645x447.jpeg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-1068x740.jpeg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-460x319.jpeg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-1074x744.jpeg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-512x355.jpeg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-707x490.jpeg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-600x416.jpeg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app-500x346.jpeg 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-tickets-plus-app.jpeg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-customized-check-in-experience\"><strong>Customized check-in experience</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets Plus lets you tailor the check-in process to fit your event perfectly. Here&#8217;s how.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Firstly, you can send custom emails to your attendees. These emails can include their QR code tickets, event details, and even personal messages. It&#8217;s a great way to keep everyone in the loop and excited about your event.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to know who&#8217;s shown up? No problem. You can check real-time reports on attendee check-ins. It&#8217;s like having a bird&#8217;s-eye view of your event as it unfolds.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But here&#8217;s where it gets really cool. Remember those registration forms where you asked for extra info? Now you can use that data to make each attendee feel special. Maybe you greet them by their preferred name, or point them towards their favorite band&#8217;s stage. You could even make sure their dietary needs are taken care of.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All of this contributes to making the event memorable for your attendees and ensuring that they have a great time.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-best-practices-for-a-smooth-and-secure-check-in-process\"><strong>Best practices for a smooth and secure check-in process</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Use a trusted QR code scanner:</strong> The Event Tickets Plus App is designed specifically for event management, so it understands your needs. It can quickly detect fake or duplicate tickets, ensuring only valid attendees get in. Plus, it&#8217;s regularly updated to stay ahead of potential security threats.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Teach your attendees about QR code safety:</strong> QR codes are like digital keys to your event. Remind attendees to treat them as such. Use Event Tickets Plus to send out custom emails explaining why they shouldn&#8217;t share their QR codes on social media or with friends. If someone else uses their code, they might not be able to get in.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Double-check who&#8217;s who:</strong> While QR codes are great, adding an extra layer of security can give you peace of mind. You might wish to verify attendees with a photo ID or email confirmation alongside their QR code.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Train your team well:</strong> Your staff is the face of your event during check-in. Make sure they&#8217;re confident handling the process. Practice makes perfect, so consider setting up mock check-in sessions to help your team work out any kinks.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Have a Plan B:</strong> Technology is amazing, but it&#8217;s not infallible. Always have a backup plan. Keep a printed guest list on hand, sorted alphabetically for quick reference. Have extra portable chargers for your scanning devices. Consider having a few spare devices loaded with your scanning app. The key is to be prepared for any hiccup so that your check-in process never comes to a complete halt.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Set up for success: </strong>Think about your check-in area as a mini-event in itself. Position multiple scanners strategically to keep lines moving. If possible, set up different lines for different types of tickets or attendee groups. Use clear, visible signage to direct people where they need to go.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Keep your tech up-to-date:</strong> Before your event, check for updates to your Event Tickets Plus app or any other software you&#8217;re using.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Run a full system test: </strong>Scan some sample QR codes, check that attendance is being recorded correctly, and make sure all devices are syncing properly. Do this well in advance of your event so you have time to troubleshoot if needed. On the day of the event, arrive early to do one final tech check before the doors open.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Manage the flow:</strong> Think about your venue layout and how people will move through it. If possible, set up multiple entry points and consider staggered entry times for different groups to prevent a massive rush all at once. Have staff available to direct traffic and answer questions. If you&#8217;re dealing with a large crowd, consider using barriers or ropes to create organized queues. The goal is to keep people moving steadily without creating bottlenecks.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-common-pain-points-in-event-entry-management\"><strong>Common pain points in event entry management</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s face it: Managing event entry can be a challenge. Even seasoned event pros run into bumps along the way.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But don&#8217;t worry – understanding these common problems is the first step to solving them. Let&#8217;s look at some of the biggest headaches in event entry management and explore how QR code technology can help smooth things out.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-offline-validation\"><strong>Offline validation</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Offline validation means checking tickets without an internet connection. Sounds great, but it can be tricky. Without the internet, validating tickets can slow to a crawl, leaving your attendees stuck in long lines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s how to tackle this:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Send out QR codes early. This way, attendees can have them ready on their phones before they even arrive.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ask folks to pull up their QR codes while they&#8217;re waiting in line. It saves time when they reach the front.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Having said that, even with Event Tickets Plus, you need an internet connection to check people in. So what can you do? You&#8217;ve got two options:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Use mobile devices with their own internet connection.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Make sure your venue has rock-solid Wi-Fi (this is your best bet).</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Want more details? Check out our <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/qr-codes-and-ticket-check-in-v1/\">guide on QR codes and ticket check-in</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-multiple-entry-points\"><strong>Multiple entry points</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Multiple entry points help spread people out and prevent annoying bottlenecks. But they come with their own challenges. How do you keep everything organized? How do you make sure security is tight at every entrance?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With Event Tickets Plus, you can set up QR code scanners at each entrance. This keeps your check-in process consistent and secure, no matter which door people use.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Want to set this up? It&#8217;s easy. Just add <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/qr-codes-and-ticket-check-in-v1/\">multiple users as Contributors to your WordPress site</a>. They&#8217;ll be ready to scan and go!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-real-example-of-overcoming-challenges-wordcamp-us-pride-party\"><strong>Real example of overcoming challenges: WordCamp US Pride Party</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want an example of how this works in real life, here are some details on how the <a href=\"https://www.theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/featured-calendar-wordcamp-us-pride-party/\">WordCamp US Pride Party</a> used Event Tickets to nail their entry process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s what they did:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>They included a QR code with each ticket confirmation.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>They had multiple staff at the door, each with the Event Tickets Plus app on their phone.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Attendees showed their QR code email on their phones, staff scanned it, and in they went.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>But what if someone couldn&#8217;t find their email? No problem. Staff could search the RSVPs on the app and check people in manually using their registration info.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"473\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-473x1024.png\" alt=\"QR code included with each ticket confirmation\" class=\"wp-image-2545691\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-473x1024.png 473w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-139x300.png 139w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-39x85.png 39w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-709x1536.png 709w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-430x931.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-645x1396.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-460x996.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-512x1109.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-509x1102.png 509w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-245x530.png 245w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-370x800.png 370w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin-500x1083.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/wordcamp-pride-party-event-tickets-qr-code-checkin.png 739w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 473px) 100vw, 473px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It was smooth, quick, and made for happy attendees. That&#8217;s the power of smart event entry management!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-amplify-your-event-s-success-with-event-tickets-plus\"><strong>Amplify your event&#8217;s success with Event Tickets Plus</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>QR code validation is about more than just keeping lines moving or stopping fake tickets. It&#8217;s about creating a smooth, secure experience that sets the tone for your entire event.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is where <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets Plus</a> shines. It takes all the power of QR code validation and wraps it up in an easy-to-use package. You get lightning-fast check-ins, top-notch security, and real-time updates on who&#8217;s walking through your doors.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to take your events to the next level? <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Give Event Tickets Plus</a> a try. See for yourself how it can transform your check-in process, boost security, and make your events run like clockwork!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/qr-code-for-ticket-validation/\">QR Code Mastery for Event Professionals</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Community 5.0.2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:148:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/community-events/community-5-0-2/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 29 Aug 2024 15:07:10 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Community Events\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545701\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:563:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release The latest Community version sets the global $post variable with the event when on the Event Submission page to fix issues with third-party plugins. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✅ Fixes Bugs squashed in this release: ⚙️ Tweaks Tweaked&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/community-events/community-5-0-2/\">Community 5.0.2</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3505:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-1 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">The latest Community version sets the global $post variable with the event when on the Event Submission page to fix issues with third-party plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-2 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Set the global $post variable with the event when on the Event Submission page to fix issues with third-party plugins.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-3 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Tweaked in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-4 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>0 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>4 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/community-events/community-5-0-2/\">Community 5.0.2</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"The Events Calendar 6.6.3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:161:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-6-3/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 29 Aug 2024 15:04:41 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"The Events Calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545700\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:581:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release The latest update of The Events Calendar adds an option to allow for duplicate Venue creation as part of creating/editing Events. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✅ Fixes Bugs squashed in this release: ⚙️ Tweaks &#160; Tweaks in this&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-6-3/\">The Events Calendar 6.6.3</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3702:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-5 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The latest update of The Events Calendar adds an option to allow for duplicate Venue creation as part of creating/editing Events.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\"> testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-6 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add an option to allow for duplicate Venue creation as part of creating/editing Events. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Character encoding issues on subscribe URLs for Outlook. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update the logic that displays the &#8220;REST API blocked&#8221; banner to reduce false positives.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Tweaks in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add docblock for make_select_box() </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Changed views: `v2/month/calendar-body/day/calendar-events/calendar-event/date`</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-8 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>0 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-6-6-3/\">The Events Calendar 6.6.3</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"Event Ticketing Software: What to Look for\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:153:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/best-event-ticketing-software/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 28 Aug 2024 14:29:09 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Event Management\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545678\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:573:\"<p>Did you know – over 680 billion people bought event tickets online in 2023? And this number is only expected to increase in the years to come! So let&#8217;s dive into the world of event ticketing software together and help you find the best solution. We&#8217;ll look at what different platforms offer, how much they&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/best-event-ticketing-software/\">Event Ticketing Software: What to Look for</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Jaime Marchwinski\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44577:\"\n<p>Did you know – over <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/forecasts/891056/event-ticket-online-users-by-segment-worldwide\">680 billion people bought event tickets online in 2023</a>? And this number is only expected to increase in the years to come!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So let&#8217;s dive into the world of event ticketing software together and help you find the best solution. We&#8217;ll look at what different platforms offer, how much they cost, and what benefits they bring to the table. Whether you&#8217;re planning a cozy local gathering or a massive conference, we&#8217;ve got you covered.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ready to find your perfect match?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-key-features-to-look-for-in-event-ticketing-software\"><strong>Key features to look for in event ticketing software</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>So, what are these magic ingredients that can make or break your event management experience? Let&#8217;s look at the must-have features of event ticketing software.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Integration and compatibility: </strong>You want software that plays nice with what you&#8217;re already using. If you&#8217;re running a WordPress site, for example, look for ticketing software that fits right in. No one wants to spend ages figuring out how to make things work together.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>User-friendly interface:</strong> Both you and your attendees should be able to navigate the platform without pulling your hair out. The easier it is to buy tickets, the more likely people are to follow through.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Adaptability:</strong> Whether you&#8217;re planning a cozy book club meetup or a massive music festival, your ticketing software should be able to handle it. Flexibility is key here.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Flexible ticket types:</strong> VIP tickets, early bird specials, general admission – you name it. Good ticketing software makes it easy to create and manage different ticket types.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Custom registration fields:</strong> Want to know your attendees&#8217; T-shirt sizes or meal preferences? Make sure you can add custom fields to your registration forms.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Multiple payment options:</strong> The more ways people can pay, the better. Look for software that supports various payment methods like <a href=\"https://www.paypal.com/\">PayPal</a>, <a href=\"https://stripe.com/\">Stripe</a>, and even <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/apple-pay/\">Apple Pay</a> or <a href=\"https://pay.google.com/\">Google Pay</a>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Instant confirmation:</strong> No one likes to be left hanging. Your software should send out immediate confirmations and e-tickets to put your attendees&#8217; minds at ease.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Premium support:</strong> You will likely need help at some point. Look for platforms that offer solid support options to help you out of sticky situations quickly.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Comprehensive resources:</strong> A good knowledge base can be a lifesaver. Check if the platform offers tutorials, FAQs, and even a community forum where you can learn from other users.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Balancing cost vs. features:</strong> You want all the cool features, but you must also watch your budget. Look for hidden costs like per-ticket fees or transaction fees. And remember, some platforms might skimp on essential features in their free or basic plans.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-top-10-event-ticketing-software-platforms\"><strong>Top 10 event ticketing software platforms</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ve got a lineup of the top ten platforms that are making waves in the industry. Each one has its special features, so pay attention to what might work best for your events.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>P.S. You’ll notice that there’s one obvious winner, but we won’t say who yet!&nbsp;</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-1-event-tickets\"><strong>1. Event Tickets</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets</a> is a powerful <a href=\"http://wordpress.org\">WordPress</a> plugin designed to make selling tickets and managing event registrations simple and efficient. As an integrated solution within WordPress, it allows users to handle event details, ticket sales, and attendee management directly from their website.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"353\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-665x353.jpg\" alt=\"Event Tickets by The Events Calendar\" class=\"wp-image-2544859\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-665x353.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-300x159.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-140x74.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-768x408.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1536x816.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-2048x1088.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-430x228.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-645x343.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-2000x1063.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1068x567.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-460x244.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1602x851.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1074x571.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-512x272.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1611x856.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-707x376.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-600x319.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-500x266.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-key-features-and-benefits\"><strong>Key features and benefits</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Unified platform for event ticketing:</strong> By integrating event management directly within WordPress, everything from selling tickets to checking in attendees is managed in one place.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Own your ticket sales:</strong> Users can create and sell tickets without any third-party involvement, ensuring they retain full control over their ticket sales and avoid additional processing fees.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Custom registration fields: </strong>Event organizers can collect specific attendee information through custom registration fields, which allows for a tailored event experience. Additionally, with the use of shortcodes, users can display event-related blocks anywhere on their site.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Easy check-ins:</strong> According to research, <a href=\"https://www.bizzabo.com/blog/attendees-want-mobile-event-app\">67.5% of event attendees</a> believe mobile event apps are crucial. Event Tickets Plus streamlines the entry process with QR code scanning, making check-ins quick and efficient through its mobile ticketing app. This is particularly useful for managing large events and reducing wait times.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Personalized event pages: </strong>Your event is unique, and your ticketing pages should reflect that. Pair Event Tickets with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\">The Events Calendar</a> (free version available) to customize your pages to match your brand.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Ticket insights for data-driven decisions:</strong> Track ticket sales and attendance with built-in reporting tools. This helps organizers understand their event performance and make data-driven decisions for future events.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-pricing-event-tickets-offers-two-plans\"><strong>Pricing: Event Tickets offers two plans</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/event-tickets/\"><strong>Free version</strong></a><strong>:</strong> Includes the basics like customizable emails, <a href=\"https://www.paypal.com/\">PayPal</a> and <a href=\"https://stripe.com/in\">Stripe</a> payments, and simple ticket sales and RSVPs.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\"><strong>Plus version</strong></a><strong>: </strong>For just $99 a year per site, you get premium support, WooCommerce and Easy Digital Downloads integrations, digital wallet payments, customizable registration fields for capturing extra attendee information, QR code check in capabilities, and more. </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets is flexible enough to handle different types of events and gives you the tools to make ticket sales a breeze. Plus, with everything happening on your own site, you&#8217;re building your brand with every ticket sold.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-2-holdmyticket\"><strong>2. HoldMyTicket</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://sell.holdmyticket.com/\">HoldMyTicket</a> provides a robust and flexible solution for event organizers, making it easier to manage ticket sales, promote events, and engage with attendees. Whether you need digital tickets, customized printed tickets, or advanced marketing tools, HoldMyTicket has you covered.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"226\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-665x226.jpg\" alt=\"HoldMyTicket event ticketing platform\" class=\"wp-image-2545687\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-665x226.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-300x102.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-140x47.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-768x260.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-1536x521.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-2048x694.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-430x146.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-645x219.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-2000x678.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-1068x362.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-460x156.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-1602x543.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-1074x364.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-512x174.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-1611x546.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-707x240.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-600x203.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/hold-my-ticket-500x170.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-key-features-and-benefits-0\"><strong>Key features and benefits</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Multiple ticket types: </strong>HoldMyTicket offers various ticket options, including digital tickets, thermal printed tickets, paper tickets, badges, and reusable tickets. This flexibility ensures that event organizers can choose the best ticketing solution for their specific needs, from eco-friendly digital tickets to custom-designed paper tickets for branding purposes.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Comprehensive marketing tools:</strong> It integrates powerful marketing tools, including custom event pages, social media sharing, and newsletter messaging. Event organizers can create SEO-ready websites, send targeted emails, and share events on social media platforms, ensuring maximum visibility and engagement.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Interactive seating charts:</strong> For events with seating arrangements, HoldMyTicket offers interactive seating charts that allow patrons to select their seats. The system supports seat holds, exchanges, and color-coded sections, making it easy to manage and sell tickets for seated events.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Customizable event management tools: </strong>Users can create repeating events, manage multiple venues, and add event add-ons during ticket checkout. The platform also allows for internal communication and collaboration with staff members, ensuring efficient event planning and execution.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>HoldMyTicket offers a range of different products depending on your event or ticket management needs. For example, they offer the free Spark platform for event management and the Swarm app for front-end box-office-style ticket sales. While HoldMyTicket itself offers free solutions, it charges a service fee of 10–15% on top of all tickets sold through the platform. Merchants can choose to absorb some or all of this fee.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-3-tickettailor\"><strong>3. TicketTailor</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/\">TicketTailor</a> is an all-in-one event ticketing platform designed to simplify the ticketing process for both new and experienced event organizers. Packed with a wide array of features, TicketTailor aims to make event management easier and more successful.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"359\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-665x359.jpg\" alt=\"TicketTailor event management and ticketing software platform\" class=\"wp-image-2545686\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-665x359.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-300x162.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-140x76.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-768x415.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-1536x830.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-2048x1107.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-430x232.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-645x349.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-2000x1081.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-1068x577.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-460x249.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-1602x866.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-1074x581.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-512x277.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-1611x871.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-2038x1102.jpg 2038w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-707x382.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-600x324.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-tailor-500x270.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-key-features-and-benefits-1\"><strong>Key features and benefits</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Customizable event pages:</strong> Create beautiful event pages using customizable templates. Whether you&#8217;re hosting a small gathering or a large conference, Ticket Tailor&#8217;s templates ensure your event page looks professional and inviting.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Mobile responsive pages: </strong>All event pages and widgets are optimized for mobile use, allowing ticket buyers to easily purchase tickets on the go. This ensures a great experience for users accessing your event details from any device.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Public or private event listings:</strong> Manage the visibility of your events with ease. Private events can be hidden behind a password, ensuring they don&#8217;t appear in internet searches, while public events are easily accessible to everyone.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Sell add-ons and merchandise: </strong>Upsell merchandise and products before your event starts by offering add-ons during the ticket purchase process. This feature helps drive additional revenue and enhances the overall event experience for attendees.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>TicketTailor has <a href=\"https://www.tickettailor.com/pricing#price-calculator\">three pricing plans</a>. If you are hosting a free event, you can use the platform for free. For paid events, you can either purchase tickets upfront, or pay as you sell. In the first case, the more credits you purchase, the lesser the commission fees. For instance, if you buy 500 credits, the per ticket commission you have to pay is $0.52. If you purchase 1000 credits, the per ticket commission you have to pay is $0.46. And so on.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the second case, where you pay as you sell, there is a flat fee of $0.75 per ticket. The platform also offers a 50% discount for charity events and low-priced tickets.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-4-eventcube\"><strong>4. Eventcube</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventcube.io/\">Eventcube</a> is a ticketing platform designed to enhance both in-person and virtual event experiences. With features like white-label solutions, tiered ticket pricing, and integration with virtual event tools, Eventcube provides event organizers with the flexibility and tools needed to manage successful events.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"306\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-665x306.jpg\" alt=\"Eventcube ticketing platform\" class=\"wp-image-2545685\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-665x306.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-300x138.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-140x64.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-768x354.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-1536x708.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-2048x943.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-430x198.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-645x297.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-2000x921.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-1068x492.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-460x212.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-1602x738.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-1074x495.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-512x236.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-1611x742.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-707x326.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-600x276.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventcube-500x230.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-key-features-and-benefits-2\"><strong>Key features and benefits</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>White-label solutions: </strong>Eventcube allows you to fully brand your ticketing experience. With white-label options, you can customize the look and feel of your event pages to align with your brand&#8217;s identity. This feature is perfect for creating a professional and cohesive event presence.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tiered ticket pricing:</strong> Eventcube supports tiered ticket pricing, so you can set different price levels for various ticket categories. This flexibility is ideal for offering early bird discounts, VIP experiences, or group rates, helping you maximize revenue and attendance.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Promote your event: </strong>Amplify your event’s visibility and expand your reach with Eventcube’s promotional tools. Create professional and eye-catching event pages to attract potential attendees. Use built-in social media tools to spread the word and create a buzz around your event. Reach out to your audience with targeted email campaigns to increase engagement and ticket sales.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventcube.io/pricing\">Eventcube’s pricing plans</a> are as follows:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Starter plan:</strong> Zero monthly fees. Charges include 5% of the ticket transaction total.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Pro plan:</strong> $99 monthly fees. Charges include 3% of the ticket transaction total.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Enterprise plan: </strong>Custom monthly fees. Bespoke rates for large-scale events. </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-5-eventbrite\"><strong>5. Eventbrite</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/\">Eventbrite</a> has a flexible pricing structure, meaning you can choose a plan that fits your budget and event requirements. The combination of powerful features, ease of use, and extensive support makes Eventbrite a top choice for event organizers looking to create, promote, and manage successful events.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"313\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-665x313.jpg\" alt=\"Eventbrite event management platform\" class=\"wp-image-2545684\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-665x313.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-300x141.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-140x66.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-768x362.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-1536x724.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-2048x965.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-430x203.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-645x304.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-2000x943.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-1068x503.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-460x217.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-1602x755.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-1074x506.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-512x241.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-1611x759.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-707x333.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-600x283.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1-500x236.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Integrated marketing tools: </strong>Promote your events with Eventbrite&#8217;s integrated marketing tools. Share your event on social media platforms, send email invitations, and use SEO to increase visibility. Eventbrite also offers promotional tools like discount codes and special offers to boost ticket sales.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Community support and resources: </strong>Eventbrite offers extensive support through its community forums, help center, and customer service team. You can access tutorials, guides, and best practices to enhance your event planning and execution. Additionally, Eventbrite&#8217;s blog provides insights and tips from industry experts.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Flexible ticketing options: </strong>Eventbrite supports various ticket types, including general admission, VIP, and group tickets. You can also offer early bird pricing, promo codes, and donation options. This flexibility helps you cater to different audience segments and maximize revenue.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Create and customize event pages: </strong>The platform allows you to quickly create and customize event pages. With user-friendly templates and design tools, you can build professional-looking event listings that attract attendees. Add images, videos, and detailed descriptions to make your event stand out.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Eventbrite charges based on the number of tickets you sell per event:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Up to 25 tickets:</strong> The Flex plan lets you create one event and sell up to 25 tickets for free.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Up to 100 tickets: </strong>The Flex plan is at $9 per event, and lets you host one event with a maximum of 100 attendees. The Pro plan is at $29 per month, where you can host unlimited events for up to 100 people.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Up to 250 tickets:</strong> Here, the Flex plan costs $24 per event and the Pro plan costs $79 per month for up to 250 attendees.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Unlimited:</strong> The Flex plan in this case is priced at $49 per event and the Pro plan is at $159 per month.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-6-ticketbud\"><strong>6. Ticketbud</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.ticketbud.com/\">Ticketbud</a> is an all-in-one event management platform that provides flexible ticketing options, robust promotional tools, and detailed reporting features. It is suitable for a variety of events, from fundraisers to festivals.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"353\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-665x353.jpg\" alt=\"Ticketbud event ticketing and management platform\" class=\"wp-image-2545683\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-665x353.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-300x159.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-140x74.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-768x407.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-1536x815.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-2048x1086.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-430x228.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-645x342.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-2000x1061.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-1068x566.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-460x244.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-1602x850.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-1074x570.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-512x272.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-1611x854.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-707x375.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-600x318.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticketbud-500x265.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-key-features-and-benefits-3\"><strong>Key features and benefits</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Landing pages for multiple events:</strong> TicketBud allows you to create landing pages to cross-promote multiple events or feature multi-day events. You can toggle between event tile lists and interactive calendar views, providing a user-friendly experience for potential attendees. This feature is ideal for organizations that host multiple events throughout the year.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Create hybrid and virtual events: </strong>With TicketBud’s <a href=\"https://zoom.us/\">Zoom</a> integration, you can easily create virtual passes for live events, allowing more people to participate online. This feature supports the growing trend of hybrid events, combining in-person and virtual attendance.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Add sponsor logos:</strong> Promote your sponsors by adding their logos to your event page. This feature enhances your event’s professionalism and helps you secure sponsorship deals by providing visible recognition for your sponsors.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Organization structure:</strong> Manage multiple organizations under your account. This feature allows you to promote events exclusively under different organizations, venues, or locations, providing flexibility and organization for event managers handling diverse portfolios.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Timed entry ticketing: </strong>Maximize attendance and maintain limited capacity with timed entry ticketing. This feature allows you to create tickets that provide access at specific times, helping to manage crowd flow and enhance attendee experience at large events.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Ticketbud has a free plan for free events. It’s <a href=\"https://www.ticketbud.com/pricing/\">premium plans</a> are as follows:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Paid events</strong>: Attendees pay 2% +99c per ticket sold.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Non-profits and schools</strong>: Attendees pay 1.75% +99c per ticket sold.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>In both cases, there’s a payment processor fee of 2.9% +30c for each ticket. However, the platform has the option to let organizers pass the commission costs to the attendees or absorb them. So the scenario would be:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Case A: Attendees pay the commission costs.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The base price of a ticket is $20. The list price of the ticket becomes $22.35 where the customer pays the additional $2.35 and the organizer earns $20 per ticket.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Case B: Organizers pay the commission costs.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The list price of the ticket is $20. The organizer pays $2.35 and earns $17.65 per ticket.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-7-eventzilla\"><strong>7. Eventzilla</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventzilla.net/\">Eventzilla</a> is a versatile event ticketing platform that allows organizers to create, promote, and manage events of all sizes with customizable registration forms, marketing integrations, and real-time analytics.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"261\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-665x261.jpg\" alt=\"Eventzilla event registration and marketing platform\" class=\"wp-image-2545682\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-665x261.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-300x118.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-140x55.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-768x301.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-1536x602.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-2048x803.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-430x169.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-645x253.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-2000x784.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-1068x419.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-460x180.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-1602x628.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-1074x421.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-512x201.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-1611x632.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-707x277.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-600x235.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventzilla-500x196.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-key-features-and-benefits-4\"><strong>Key features and benefits</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Custom event registration pages:</strong> Create a stunning event registration page in minutes with Eventzilla’s easy-to-use templates. Customize your event details with images, videos, ticket options, maps, and social links, ensuring your event page looks professional and inviting.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Multiple event registrations: </strong>Eventzilla supports multiple registration flows based on attendee types, including self-service options for registration, modification, cancellation, and refunds. This feature ensures a smooth and flexible registration experience for all participants.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Account-free registration: </strong>Provide a hassle-free registration experience for your attendees. Eventzilla’s mobile-friendly registration pages do not require attendees to create an account, making the registration process quick and simple. </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Embed registration widgets:</strong> Easily embed registration widgets on your blog, website, or even <a href=\"http://facebook.com\">Facebook</a> page. This feature allows attendees to register without leaving your site, providing a seamless experience and increasing your event’s visibility.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Advanced event management: </strong>Eventzilla provides a multi-track event schedule builder, allowing you to create flexible schedules with multiple parallel tracks and sessions. Publish rich speaker profiles and customize each session with advanced enrollment options. The platform also offers comprehensive dashboards and custom reports, integrating with <a href=\"https://analytics.google.com/analytics/academy/\">Google Analytics</a> for detailed tracking of sales, visits, and referrals.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Eventzilla’s Basic plan starts at $1.75 per ticket and its Plus plan costs 1.45% + $0.75 per ticket. The platform also has custom pricing plans for larger events.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-8-ticketsource\"><strong>8. TicketSource</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.ticketsource.co.uk/\">TicketSource</a> offers a comprehensive online ticketing service designed for events of all sizes, featuring secure payment processing, customizable event pages, and detailed sales reporting.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"343\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-665x343.jpg\" alt=\"TicketSource event ticketing platform\" class=\"wp-image-2545680\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-665x343.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-300x155.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-140x72.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-768x396.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-1536x793.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-2048x1057.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-430x222.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-645x333.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-2000x1032.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-1068x551.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-460x237.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-1602x827.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-1074x554.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-512x264.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-1611x831.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-707x365.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-600x310.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/ticket-source-500x258.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-key-features-and-benefits-5\"><strong>Key features and benefits</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>General admission and allocated seating:</strong> Whether you prefer general admission or allocated seating, TicketSource has you covered. Sell unallocated tickets from a quota or let customers choose their preferred seats from an onscreen layout of your venue. This flexibility helps cater to different event types and attendee preferences.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Telephone box office service: </strong>For customers who prefer not to book online, TicketSource offers a Telephone Box Office service. This service handles booking phone calls on your behalf and answers basic queries, reducing the pressure on your own customer service team.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Sell merchandise and extras:</strong> Enhance the attendee experience by offering sundry items such as programs, merchandise, and pre-show meals during the booking process. TicketSource allows you to monitor stock levels and bundle extras with tickets, encouraging additional purchases and ensuring customer satisfaction.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Waiting list feature: </strong>Manage interest for sold-out events with TicketSource’s waiting list feature. This tool allows you to record ticket interest from customers, ensuring you can take advantage of opportunities to accommodate more attendees, such as returned tickets or additional dates.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.ticketsource.us/pricing\">TicketSource charges</a> 3.5% + 0.99c per ticket, including all processing costs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-why-event-tickets-stands-out\"><strong>Why Event Tickets stands out</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets isn&#8217;t just another ticketing platform. It&#8217;s a powerful tool that gives you full control over your events. Let&#8217;s look at what makes it special.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-advanced-features\"><strong>Advanced features</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets can handle ticketing for events of all sizes and works for both in-person and online events.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can add custom fields to your registration forms, create personalized emails, and set up different ticket types, so the ticketing process can perfectly fit your event.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, its mobile app is very strong. Both you and your attendees can use it on phones and tablets. The QR code feature makes check-ins quick and easy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you want to know how your event is doing, Event Tickets has great reporting tools. You can track ticket sales, see who&#8217;s attending, and more. This helps you make smart decisions for your events.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-user-experience-and-usability\"><strong>User experience and usability</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets is easy to set up and use. You don&#8217;t need to be tech-savvy to get started. The interface is clear and simple.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the best things about Event Tickets is that you can host it on your own website. This means you don&#8217;t need to use other platforms. You keep control of your data and your brand.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Need help? Event Tickets has great customer support. You can get help through live chat, email, or phone. There&#8217;s also a lot of helpful information through guides and in the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/\">knowledgebase</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-cost-effectiveness\"><strong>Cost-effectiveness</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets Plus doesn&#8217;t charge you for each ticket you sell. Instead, you pay a flat yearly fee. This makes it easier to plan your budget and could save you a lot of money, especially for bigger events.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-real-world-use-cases-wordcamp-us-pride-party\"><strong>Real-world use cases: WordCamp US Pride Party</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Picture this: It&#8217;s 2023, and the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/featured-calendar-wordcamp-us-pride-party/\">WordCamp US Pride Party</a> is in full swing. But here&#8217;s the catch — 2,000 eager WordCamp attendees are vying for just 400 coveted party spots. Talk about a hot ticket!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The organizers knew they needed a rock-solid plan. Enter Event Tickets.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>They whipped up a sleek WordPress site using the <a href=\"https://www.kadencewp.com/\">Kadence theme</a>, featuring an irresistible RSVP form front and center. With Event Tickets at the helm, they effortlessly collected data, managed RSVPs, and fired off personalized email confirmations packed with all the party particulars.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But the real showstopper was the Event Tickets Plus mobile app.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With this nifty tool, organizers breezed through check-ins using QR codes. No more endless queues, just happy partygoers ready to mingle!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2023 bash was such a hit they did it all over again in June 2024. This time, 793 people signed up for the <a href=\"https://rsvp.lgbt/\">WCEU 2024 Pride Party</a>. The organizers cranked up the excitement by showcasing attendees on the website, sparking a buzz that had everyone talking before the first beat dropped.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This real-life party proves that with Event Tickets, you can kiss ticketing troubles goodbye and focus on throwing an unforgettable shindig. Now, that&#8217;s something to celebrate!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-take-the-next-step-with-event-tickets\"><strong>Take the next step with Event Tickets</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Having the right event ticketing platform can make a world of difference for event organizers, making the entire event management process smoother and more efficient.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s why Event Tickets is so great. It&#8217;s flexible, cost-effective, and packed with features that work perfectly with WordPress. This makes it a powerful tool for managing ticket sales, whether you&#8217;re planning a small meetup or a big conference.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, if you are ready to make your next event a breeze, why not <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">give Event Tickets a try today</a>? It could be the solution you&#8217;ve been looking for in your event planning toolkit.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/best-event-ticketing-software/\">Event Ticketing Software: What to Look for</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"Events Calendar Pro 7.0.2.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:163:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-7-0-2-1/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 26 Aug 2024 22:17:30 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Events Calendar Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545635\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:595:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release This latest version of Events Calendar Pro includes an important security fix that prevents PHP Object Serialization exploits for Widgets on Legacy Support. See this Blog for more details and which versions have been updated. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-7-0-2-1/\">Events Calendar Pro 7.0.2.1</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2913:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">This latest version of Events Calendar Pro includes an important security fix that prevents PHP Object Serialization exploits for Widgets on Legacy Support.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>See this <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/important-security-update-for-the-events-calendar-pro/\">Blog</a> for more details and which versions have been updated.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-10 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Prevents PHP Object Serialization exploit for Widgets on Legacy Support.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-11 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files, strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>0 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-7-0-2-1/\">Events Calendar Pro 7.0.2.1</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"Important Security Update for The Events Calendar Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:165:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/important-security-update-for-the-events-calendar-pro/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 26 Aug 2024 22:16:28 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"What\'s New\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545634\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:602:\"<p>Here at The Events Calendar we take security very seriously. We’re always on the lookout for potential threats and take swift action to resolve any issues we find or that are brought to our attention. On Tuesday, August 20 we received a report notifying us of a potentially serious vulnerability in The Events Calendar Pro.&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/important-security-update-for-the-events-calendar-pro/\">Important Security Update for The Events Calendar Pro</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Nathan B. Weller\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5024:\"\n<p>Here at The Events Calendar we take security very seriously. We’re always on the lookout for potential threats and take swift action to resolve any issues we find or that are brought to our attention.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On Tuesday, August 20 we received a report notifying us of a potentially serious vulnerability in The Events Calendar Pro. Since then our team has been hard at work resolving the issue.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>If you’re using The Events Calendar Pro plugin it is important that you follow the instructions in this post as soon as possible.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-vulnerability\">The vulnerability</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The vulnerability lies in how the plugin handles PHP Object Serialization for widgets. If left unpatched, attackers could leverage this as a vector for Remote Code Execution (RCE). This means that even users with limited permissions, such as those assigned the &#8220;Contributor&#8221; role, could exploit this vulnerability depending on the combination of third-party plugins in use on your site. However, it’s important to note that this exploit can only be carried out if attackers can create new widgets.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-who-s-affected\">Who’s affected?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Everyone running The Events Calendar Pro is affected by this vulnerability.</strong> We have created a patch for the latest version plus the four previous feature versions that some of you may still be using.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>7.0.2 &#8211; current version</li>\n\n\n\n<li>6.5.1 &#8211; legacy version</li>\n\n\n\n<li>6.4.0.1  &#8211; legacy version</li>\n\n\n\n<li>6.3.3  &#8211; legacy version</li>\n\n\n\n<li>6.2.4  &#8211; legacy version</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are running an even older version than those listed above and need to update please <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/\">reach out to support</a> with the exact version.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-solution\">The solution</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are two solutions for resolving this issue. The first and easiest is to simply make sure you are running the latest version of The Events Calendar Pro plugin. Go to <strong>WP Admin &gt; Updates</strong> and update to version 7.0.2.1. The second solution is for anyone who needs to remain on a legacy version of The Events Calendar Pro for compatibility reasons. To address that need we have released patches for each of the legacy versions listed above.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Events Calendar Pro Patches:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Update from 7.0.2 to 7.0.2.1 &#8211; can be done from <strong>WP Admin > Updates</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update from 6.5.1 to 6.5.1.1</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update from 6.4.0.1 to 6.4.0.2</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update from 6.3.3 to 6.3.3.1</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update from 6.2.4 to 6.2.4.1</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>To implement the patched copy of The Events Calendar Pro plugin for your specific legacy version, please do the following as soon as possible:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Sign into your account here at theeventscalendar.com</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Navigate to <strong>My Account > Downloads</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Download the patched plugin files for the legacy version of The Events Calendar Pro you’re running (as listed above)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>On your website navigate to <strong>WP Admin > Plugins > Add New Plugin</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click the “Upload Plugin” button at the top of the page</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click “Choose File” and select the zipped folder you downloaded from The Events Calendar</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click “Install Now”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click “Replace current with uploaded”</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Patch installed!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-thank-you-to-wordfence\">Thank you to WordFence</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We’d like to thank WordFence for bringing this vulnerability to our attention. It’s through the combined effort of plugin creators, WordPress security companies, independent researchers, and security minded users that we’re all made safer online. Thank you!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-stay-safe-out-there\">Stay safe out there</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We also want to thank you, our customers, for the trust you extend to us. You can depend on us to always prioritize security in our products and notify you of any action needed to keep your website and data safe. If you have any questions or concerns (or something to report) you can always reach out to us <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On a more general note, instances like this are a good reminder to review and implement WordPress security best practices across the board. If that’s something you haven’t done lately, we recommend <a href=\"https://solidwp.com/blog/wordpress-security-the-ultimate-guide/\">this guide</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/important-security-update-for-the-events-calendar-pro/\">Important Security Update for The Events Calendar Pro</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"Your Go-To WordPress Event Registration Guide\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:152:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/wordpress-event-registration/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 23 Aug 2024 17:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Event Management\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545614\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:659:\"<p>Event registration allows organizers to collect important information from attendees, ensuring a smooth check-in process and overall event experience. However, managing registrations can be challenging without the right tools. WordPress can be a user-friendly, highly customizable, and cost-effective solution for event registration and it’s a go-to choice for many event organizers. Plus, it boasts a&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/wordpress-event-registration/\">Your Go-To WordPress Event Registration Guide</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"Jaime Marchwinski\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58480:\"\n<p>Event registration allows organizers to collect important information from attendees, ensuring a smooth check-in process and overall event experience. However, managing registrations can be challenging without the right tools.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\">WordPress</a> can be a user-friendly, highly customizable, and cost-effective solution for event registration and it’s a go-to choice for many event organizers. Plus, it boasts a wide range of powerful plugins designed specifically for event management.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this guide, we&#8217;ll explore the best WordPress event registration plugins available. We&#8217;ll focus on setting up an effective registration page and address common challenges event organizers face, such as managing RSVPs, handling ticket sales, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether it’s a small workshop or a large conference, let’s discover all the knowledge and tools you need to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/managing-event-registrations-on-wordpress/\">create a seamless registration experience</a> for your attendees!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-best-wordpress-event-registration-plugins\"><strong>The best WordPress event registration plugins</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to managing event registrations on WordPress, choosing the right plugin can make all the difference. These tools can save you time, streamline your processes, and enhance the experience for you and your attendees. Let’s take a look at key features, ease of use, and the ability to tackle common event management challenges.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-1-event-tickets\"><strong>1. Event Tickets</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets</a> is a powerful and user-friendly plugin that handles event registration, ticketing, and attendee management. It works perfectly with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/\">The Events Calendar</a>, making it an excellent choice for those already using the most popular calendar plugin for WordPress.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"353\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-665x353.jpg\" alt=\"Event Tickets by The Events Calendar\" class=\"wp-image-2544859\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-665x353.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-300x159.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-140x74.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-768x408.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1536x816.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-2048x1088.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-430x228.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-645x343.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-2000x1063.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1068x567.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-460x244.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1602x851.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1074x571.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-512x272.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-1611x856.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-707x376.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-600x319.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/07/event-tickets-home-page-500x266.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Attendee registration forms: </strong>Collect essential attendee information, from names and emails to T-shirt sizes and food preferences, ensuring you have all the details you need to provide a personalized event experience.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Mobile ticketing app:</strong> With <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/using-qr-codes-with-event-tickets-plus/\">the QR check-in feature</a>, managing event check-ins becomes seamless and efficient, enhancing the day-of-event management experience.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Ticket stock countdown:</strong> Keep your audience informed about ticket availability with automatic ticket counts, encouraging timely purchases and reducing the risk of overselling.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Ticket insights: </strong>Generate detailed sales and attendee reports to gain valuable insights into your event&#8217;s performance.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Customized email confirmation: </strong>Send no-code, personalized ticket confirmations to keep your attendees updated and engaged.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Attendee-only content:</strong> Restrict certain information, like virtual event links or registration details, to attendees only, ensuring exclusive access to your event content.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-why-choose-event-tickets-for-your-wordpress-site\"><strong>Why choose Event Tickets for your WordPress site?</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets stands out as a comprehensive solution for WordPress event management because:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It gives you a unified platform for all your event needs, combining event planning, ticketing, and attendee tracking in one powerful plugin.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>With <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/tips/styling-an-event-registration-form-for-wordpress/\">extensive customization options</a>, you can tailor registration forms, emails, and ticket types to fit your specific needs.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Its intuitive interface makes creating even complex ticketing tiers a breeze.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It doesn’t break the bank. You can start with the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress/the-best-free-event-tickets-plugins-for-wordpress/\">free version</a> for your monthly networking events and upgrade to Plus when you&#8217;re ready to host a ticketed conference with <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/how-to-create-custom-registration-forms/\">custom registration fields</a>.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/featured-calendar-whisk-cooking-classes/\">Whisk</a>, a popular cooking class provider, uses Event Tickets Plus to manage their ticket sales. They utilize the Attendee Registration template to gather essential information like names, email addresses, and dietary restrictions from participants.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"628\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-665x628.png\" alt=\"Registration form for Whisk’s cooking classes, created with Event Tickets Plus\" class=\"wp-image-2545630\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-665x628.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-300x283.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-90x85.png 90w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-768x725.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-430x406.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-645x609.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-1068x1009.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-460x434.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-1074x1014.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-512x484.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-1167x1102.png 1167w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-561x530.png 561w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-600x567.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form-500x472.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/whisk-cooking-classes-registration-form.png 1276w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets integrates smoothly with standard payment gateways and works seamlessly with WordPress and <a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/\">WooCommerce</a>. You can start with the free version and upgrade to Plus for advanced features like custom registration fields and QR code check-in via a mobile app.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With access to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/\">premium support</a> and detailed documentation, you&#8217;ll have all the help you need to set up and run your events successfully. To explore pricing options and learn more, visit the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets feature page</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-2-eventbrite\"><strong>2. Eventbrite</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/\">Eventbrite</a> is a popular event management platform that can be integrated into your WordPress site. This option is perfect for those who prefer to manage their events through Eventbrite&#8217;s platform while showcasing them on their WordPress website. Note that you need a specialist plugin to integrate Eventbrite with WordPress – you can use the popular ‘widget for Eventbrite API’, aka the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/widget-for-eventbrite-api/\">Display Eventbrite Events</a> plugin, for this.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"313\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-665x313.jpg\" alt=\"Eventbrite event registration and management platform\" class=\"wp-image-2545629\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-665x313.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-300x141.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-140x66.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-768x362.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1536x724.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-2048x965.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-430x203.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-645x304.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-2000x943.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1068x503.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-460x217.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1602x755.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1074x506.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-512x241.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-1611x759.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-707x333.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-600x283.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/eventbrite-event-management-platform-500x236.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Easy event creation:</strong> Eventbrite simplifies the process of creating events with an intuitive interface that guides organizers through each step. You can quickly set up event pages, customize ticket types, and add event details without any technical expertise.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Customizable event pages: </strong>Eventbrite provides customizable event pages that allow you to add your branding, images, and videos. You can also use templates to ensure a professional look and feel for your event.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Flexible ticketing options:</strong> Eventbrite supports various ticket types, including free, paid, and donation-based tickets. Organizers can set different price points, offer discounts, and create promotional codes to attract more attendees.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Integrated marketing tools:</strong> Eventbrite offers built-in marketing tools to help you promote your event. These include email marketing, social media integration, and search engine optimization (SEO) to increase visibility and reach a broader audience.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Benefits of the WordPress-Eventbrite integration:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Tap into Eventbrite&#8217;s ecosystem:</strong> Eventbrite&#8217;s vast user base can boost your event&#8217;s visibility. For instance, if you&#8217;re organizing a niche conference, Eventbrite&#8217;s discovery features can help attract attendees who might not find your event through other channels.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Brand consistency across platforms: </strong>Keep your brand look and feel consistent whether visitors are on your WordPress site or Eventbrite. This is particularly useful for established brands hosting multiple events. Imagine a university using this integration to maintain a cohesive look across all its departmental events.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Streamlined promotion and sales:</strong> Eventbrite&#8217;s marketing tools can simplify your promotional efforts. For example, if you&#8217;re running a series of workshops, you can easily create email campaigns, social media posts, and even paid ads directly from the Eventbrite platform.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Mobile management:</strong> With Eventbrite&#8217;s mobile app, you can manage your event on the go. This is particularly handy for multi-day conferences where you might need to make last-minute changes or check real-time attendance data.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>While Eventbrite offers powerful features, it&#8217;s important to consider the costs, especially for paid events. Eventbrite charges a fee per ticket sold, which can impact your bottom line for larger events.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-3-events-manager\"><strong>3. Events Manager</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/events-manager/\">Events Manager</a> provides a comprehensive set of tools to create, promote, and manage events directly from your WordPress dashboard. Suitable for both small and large-scale events, Events Manager offers extensive customization options and integrates seamlessly with various WordPress themes and plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"358\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-665x358.png\" alt=\"The Events Manager plugin for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-2545628\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-665x358.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-300x161.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-140x75.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-768x413.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-1536x827.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-430x231.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-645x347.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-1068x575.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-460x248.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-1074x578.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-512x276.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-707x380.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-600x323.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager-500x269.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/events-manager.png 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key features:</strong><br></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Booking management: </strong>The plugin includes a booking management system that supports both free and paid bookings. You can customize booking forms, set up approval processes, and send automated email notifications to attendees.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Recurring events: </strong>Create complex recurring event schedules with ease. Events Manager supports various recurrence patterns, such as daily, weekly, monthly, and custom schedules, ensuring flexibility for all types of events.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Location management:</strong> Manage event locations with detailed information, including addresses, maps, and images. You can reuse locations for multiple events and display them on your site with <a href=\"https://maps.google.com/\">Google Maps</a> integration.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Multisite support:</strong> Events Manager supports WordPress multisite installations, enabling centralized event management across multiple sites.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the main benefits of the Events Manager plugin is that it significantly enhances event visibility through SEO-friendly event pages and social sharing options, helping you reach a broader audience. Additionally, the plugin saves you valuable time by automating the booking and notification processes, reducing the need for manual effort and allowing you to focus on other important tasks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the flip side, if you&#8217;re managing very large events or dealing with a high volume of bookings, you might experience some performance slowdowns. However, while these issues can be a bit frustrating, they don&#8217;t overshadow the overall functionality and benefits of the plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-4-event-espresso\"><strong>4. Event Espresso</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://eventespresso.com/\">Event Espresso</a> takes the hassle out of event management and registration. It&#8217;s designed to be your all-in-one solution, handling everything from ticketing to attendee management.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"372\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-665x372.jpg\" alt=\"Event Espresso event management plugin for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-2545627\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-665x372.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-300x168.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-140x78.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-768x429.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-1536x859.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-430x240.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-645x361.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-1068x597.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-460x257.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-1602x895.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-1074x600.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-512x286.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-1611x900.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-1972x1102.jpg 1972w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-707x395.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-600x335.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso-500x279.jpg 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/event-espresso.jpg 1977w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Multiple ticket options: </strong>The plugin supports multiple ticket types and pricing options, enabling you to offer early bird pricing, group discounts, and more. This flexibility helps cater to different audience segments and maximize ticket sales.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Customizable registration forms:</strong> Event Espresso allows you to create custom registration forms to collect specific information from your attendees. You can add various fields such as text inputs, checkboxes, and dropdowns to gather essential details. Planning a food festival? You can easily add fields for dietary restrictions or food preferences to ensure every attendee is catered for.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Integrated payment gateways: </strong>Event Espresso integrates with a variety of payment gateways, including PayPal, Stripe, and <a href=\"http://authorize.net\">Authorize.net</a>, allowing you to securely process payments online. It also supports offline payment methods like checks and invoices.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Calendar and event listings:</strong> Display your events on a calendar or as a list on your website. The calendar view provides a visual representation of upcoming events, while the list view offers detailed information about each event.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>While Event Espresso has several useful features, it does come with a steeper learning curve compared to some simpler plugins. However, for those needing strong event management capabilities, the initial time investment can pay off in the long run.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-5-mightyforms\"><strong>5. MightyForms</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mightyforms.com/\">MightyForms</a> is a versatile form builder plugin that brings event registration to life on your WordPress site. With its user-friendly drag-and-drop interface, you can create sophisticated registration forms without any coding knowledge.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"365\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-665x365.jpg\" alt=\"MightyForms form builder plugin for WordPress\" class=\"wp-image-2545626\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-665x365.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-300x165.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-140x77.jpg 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-768x422.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-1536x843.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-2048x1124.jpg 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-430x236.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-645x354.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-2000x1098.jpg 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-1068x586.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-460x253.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-1602x880.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-1074x590.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-512x281.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-1611x885.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-2007x1102.jpg 2007w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-707x388.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-600x329.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/mighty-forms-500x275.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Drag-and-drop form builder:</strong> MightyForms offers a user-friendly drag-and-drop form builder that allows you to create forms quickly and easily. You can add various form fields, such as text inputs, dropdowns, checkboxes, and file uploads, then arrange them to suit your design.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Customizable templates: </strong>Choose from a wide range of pre-built templates tailored for different industries and use cases. Customize these templates to match your branding and requirements, saving time and effort in form creation.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Real-time data capture:</strong> Capture data in real-time and receive instant notifications when a form is submitted. This feature ensures that you never miss a response and can take timely action based on the collected data.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Conditional logic:</strong> Enhance your forms with conditional logic to show or hide fields based on user responses. This makes your forms more dynamic and user-friendly, providing a personalized experience for each respondent.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Integrations: </strong>MightyForms integrates with popular third-party applications and services, including <a href=\"https://workspace.google.com/intl/en_in/products/sheets/\">Google Sheets</a>, <a href=\"https://mailchimp.com/\">Mailchimp</a>, <a href=\"https://www.salesforce.com/in/\">Salesforce</a>, and <a href=\"https://zapier.com/\">Zapier</a>. These integrations allow you to automate workflows and sync form data with your preferred tools.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s worth noting that MightyForms is not specifically designed for event management. This means you might need to combine it with other tools for comprehensive event planning.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-6-registrationmagic\"><strong>6. RegistrationMagic</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://registrationmagic.com/\">RegistrationMagic</a> specializes in creating highly customizable registration forms. It provides a set of tools to create custom registration forms, manage user data, and automate registration workflows. The plugin is perfect for event organizers who need detailed control over their registration process and want to collect specific information from attendees.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"442\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-665x442.jpg\" alt=\"RegistrationMagic – WordPress user registration plugin\" class=\"wp-image-2545625\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-665x442.jpg 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-300x199.jpg 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-128x85.jpg 128w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-768x511.jpg 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-1536x1021.jpg 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-480x320.jpg 480w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-240x160.jpg 240w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-720x480.jpg 720w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-1528x1016.jpg 1528w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-764x508.jpg 764w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-430x286.jpg 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-645x429.jpg 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-1068x710.jpg 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-460x306.jpg 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-1602x1065.jpg 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-1074x714.jpg 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-512x340.jpg 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-1611x1071.jpg 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-1658x1102.jpg 1658w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-707x470.jpg 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-600x399.jpg 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic-500x332.jpg 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/registration-magic.jpg 1736w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Key features:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Custom form builder:</strong> RegistrationMagic offers an intuitive drag-and-drop form builder that allows you to create custom registration forms with ease. You can add various fields, including text inputs, dropdowns, checkboxes, and file uploads, to capture the information you need from users.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Multiple form management:</strong> Create and manage multiple registration forms with unique settings and configurations. This feature is especially useful for websites that need different forms for different purposes, such as event registrations, membership sign-ups, and surveys.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>User role assignment: </strong>Automatically assign specific user roles upon registration, ensuring users have the appropriate permissions and access levels based on their registration type.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Multi-page forms: </strong>Create multi-page forms to break down lengthy registration processes into manageable steps. This improves the user experience and reduces form abandonment rates.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Security features:</strong> Ensure the security of your registration forms with features like Google reCAPTCHA, custom password policies, and data encryption.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Having said that, although RegistrationMagic offers extensive customization options, it has a steeper learning curve compared to simpler plugins. However, for events that require complex registration processes or detailed attendee information, the initial time investment in setting up RegistrationMagic can lead to a more tailored registration experience for your attendees.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-setting-up-your-event-registration-page-with-event-tickets\"><strong>Setting up your event registration page with Event Tickets</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that we&#8217;ve explored some of the top WordPress event registration plugins, let&#8217;s focus on how to <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qpfJ1vEhIg0\">create an event with online registration</a> using <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-creating-an-events-page-with-rsvp\"><strong>Creating an events page with RSVP</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s start by creating an event page with RSVP options using Event Tickets. There are two ways to do this:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>You can set up tickets for an event created using an event plugin, like The Events Calendar.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can create a simple page displaying a poster of your event with all the details and add a tickets block there. </li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>First, let’s talk about the second scenario:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Navigate to <em>Pages > Add New Page</em>. This will create a new page for your event.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Give your event a catchy title and write a detailed description. Remember, the more information you provide, the more likely people are to attend!</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add the date, time, location, etc., for your event.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-665x315.png\" alt=\"Event invitation created using a standard WordPress page template\" class=\"wp-image-2545624\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-665x315.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-300x142.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-140x66.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-768x363.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-1536x727.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-2048x969.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-430x203.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-645x305.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-2000x946.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-1068x505.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-460x218.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-1602x758.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-1074x508.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-512x242.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-1611x762.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-707x335.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-600x284.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-invitation-page-500x237.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>If you&#8217;re using <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/\">The Events Calendar</a> alongside Event Tickets, you&#8217;ll find much more streamlined options to create the event and add all the relevant details.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"600\" height=\"417\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/generic-event-created-with-tec.gif\" alt=\"Event invitation created with The Events Calendar\" class=\"wp-image-2545623\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now let’s add an RSVP registration form.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>If you create the event on a page, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ho0FMu8vLHg\">add RSVP options directly</a> using an <em>RSVP</em> block. If you create the event using the event editor, you&#8217;ll see an option to add RSVP tickets.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"655\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-665x655.png\" alt=\"RSVP block for page\" class=\"wp-image-2545622\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-665x655.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-300x295.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-86x85.png 86w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-768x756.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-430x424.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-645x635.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-460x453.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-512x504.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-538x530.png 538w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-600x591.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page-500x492.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/rsvp-block-for-page.png 1060w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click on this and fill in the details.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can set the RSVP capacity, start and end dates for RSVPs, and even add a description for the RSVP option.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"496\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-665x496.png\" alt=\"Add a new RSVP to an event created using The Events Calendar\" class=\"wp-image-2545621\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-665x496.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-300x224.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-114x85.png 114w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-768x573.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-260x195.png 260w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-430x321.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-645x481.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-1068x797.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-460x343.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-1074x801.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-512x382.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-707x527.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-600x448.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event-500x373.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-rsvp-to-tec-event.png 1284w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve configured these settings, publish your page. The RSVP form will automatically appear on your event page, ready for attendees to respond. It&#8217;s that simple!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-selling-and-managing-tickets\"><strong>Selling and managing tickets</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve set up your event page, it&#8217;s time to start selling tickets. Event Tickets makes this process smooth and efficient.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>To <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/making-tickets/\">create tickets</a>, go to your event and look for the <em>Tickets</em> section. Here, you can add different ticket types, set prices, and specify the number of tickets available.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can also set start and end dates for ticket sales, which is great for early-bird specials or last-minute deals.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"711\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-665x711.png\" alt=\"Add a new ticket to an event\" class=\"wp-image-2545620\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-665x711.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-281x300.png 281w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-79x85.png 79w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-768x821.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-430x460.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-645x690.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-1068x1142.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-460x492.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-1074x1149.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-512x548.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-1030x1102.png 1030w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-496x530.png 496w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-600x642.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event-500x535.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/add-new-ticket-to-tec-event.png 1153w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Event Tickets automatically sends email confirmations to attendees when they purchase a ticket. This feature keeps your attendees informed and saves you time. You can customize these emails to include important event details or special instructions.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The plugin also provides detailed reporting features. You can easily <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2DYA7SRFvQw\">track ticket sales, view attendee information</a>, and monitor your event&#8217;s performance. This data is invaluable for planning future events and understanding your audience better.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>With these tools at your fingertips, you&#8217;ll be able to manage ticket sales efficiently and keep your attendees well-informed, all while gathering useful data to improve your future events.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-customizing-your-registration-forms\"><strong>Customizing your registration forms</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets offers basic customization options, but if you want to take your registration forms to the next level, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets Plus</a> is the way to go. This premium version unlocks a wealth of advanced features, including more custom fields and <a href=\"https://woocommerce.com/\">WooCommerce</a> integration.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One standout feature of Event Tickets Plus is the <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uo6D3sJn5qQ\">Attendee Registration Settings</a>. This powerful tool allows you to gather more detailed information from your attendees using custom registration fields. Here&#8217;s how to set it up:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>While adding a new ticket, or editing an existing one, scroll down to <em>Attendee Information</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Here, you can add custom fields that ticket buyers need to enter while purchasing the ticket.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>There are various field types, such as <em>Text, Radio, Checkbox, Dropdown</em>, and some standard fields, like <em>Email, Telephone, Birth date</em>, etc.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Create a field set of the custom information you will need and add it to your ticket. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Save your changes, and these fields will now appear when attendees purchase tickets.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"600\" height=\"324\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/attendee-information-event-tickets.gif\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2545619\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>By customizing your registration forms, you can collect all the necessary information upfront, making event planning and management much easier. Whether you&#8217;re organizing a conference with multiple tracks or a wedding with specific guest requirements, these customization options ensure you&#8217;re well-prepared for your event.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-integrating-with-payment-gateways\"><strong>Integrating with payment gateways</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A smooth payment process is crucial for your event&#8217;s success, and Event Tickets has you covered. The plugin offers easy integration with popular payment gateways through its built-in eCommerce platform, <a href=\"https://www.theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/introducing-tickets-commerce-a-new-way-to-sell-tickets-for-free/\">Tickets Commerce</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Out of the box, Event Tickets supports <a href=\"https://www.paypal.com/\">PayPal</a> and <a href=\"https://stripe.com/in\">Stripe</a>, allowing you to accept a wide range of payment methods. If you need even more options, Event Tickets Plus expands your choices. It adds support for <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/apple-pay/\">Apple Pay</a> and <a href=\"https://pay.google.com/\">Google Pay</a>, and integrates with WooCommerce for even more flexibility. Given that <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/advisor/banking/digital-wallets-payment-apps/\">53% of Americans use digital wallets</a> and 78% of Gen Z shoppers say they&#8217;d stop buying from a merchant that doesn&#8217;t accept digital wallets, offering different payment gateways is extremely important.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/guide/event-tickets/\">set up your payment gateways</a>:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Go to <em>Tickets > Settings > Payments.</em></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Toggle Enable Tickets Commerce ON.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Choose the payment gateways you want to integrate.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"387\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-665x387.png\" alt=\"Enable Tickets Commerce and add your desired payment gateways to the process\" class=\"wp-image-2545618\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-665x387.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-300x175.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-140x82.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-768x448.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-1536x895.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-430x251.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-645x376.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-1068x622.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-460x268.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-1602x933.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-1074x626.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-512x298.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-1611x939.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-707x412.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-600x350.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets-500x291.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/adding-payment-gateways-event-tickets.png 1838w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"4\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Follow the prompts to connect your account.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Save your settings.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>By offering a variety of payment options, you&#8217;re making it easier for attendees to register for your event, potentially boosting your ticket sales. Remember, the easier it is to pay, the more likely people are to complete their registration!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-common-concerns-and-solutions\"><strong>Common concerns and solutions</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Many a time, setting up your event registration can feel like navigating a maze. Don&#8217;t worry, you&#8217;re not alone! Even seasoned event planners hit a few bumps along the way.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s tackle the most common head-scratchers that pop up when using Event Tickets. We&#8217;ll turn those &#8220;uh-oh&#8221; moments into &#8220;aha!&#8221; solutions, helping you breeze through your event planning like a pro.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-attendee-management\"><strong>Attendee management</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Managing attendees efficiently is crucial for a smooth event, from registration to check-in. But how do you keep track of everyone without getting overwhelmed?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets Plus comes to the rescue with its comprehensive attendee management features. Here&#8217;s how it helps:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Attendee lists:</strong> Easily track registrations and manage event capacity.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Check-in made simple: </strong>Use QR code scanning for quick and efficient entry.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Mobile ticketing:</strong> Offer digital wallets to streamline the entry process, reducing lines and wait times.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Custom registration fields:</strong> Gather specific information you need from attendees.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, if you&#8217;re running a conference, you can use custom fields to collect attendees&#8217; session preferences. Then, use the attendee list to plan room allocations. On the day of the event, speed up check-in with QR code scanning, ensuring a great first impression.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With these tools, you can focus on creating an amazing event experience, knowing your attendee management is under control.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-refunds\"><strong>Refunds</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Worried about handling refunds without causing headaches for you or your attendees? It&#8217;s a common concern, but Event Tickets has got your back!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both Event Tickets and Event Tickets Plus offer refund management features. With the free version, you can process refunds through Stripe and PayPal. If you&#8217;re using Event Tickets Plus with WooCommerce, you can handle refunds directly through your WooCommerce interface.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some tips for smooth refund handling:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Set up a clear refund policy before selling tickets.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Communicate your policy to attendees during the purchase process.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Be consistent in applying your policy to avoid disputes.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Process refunds promptly to maintain customer satisfaction.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>For step-by-step instructions on processing refunds, check out the Event Tickets documentation on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/how-to-refund-or-cancel-a-tickets-order/\">how to refund or cancel a tickets order</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-customizing-confirmation-emails\"><strong>Customizing confirmation emails</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Picture this: Your attendee just registered for your event. They&#8217;re excited, eager, and waiting for that confirmation email to hit their inbox. But when it arrives, it&#8217;s bland, generic, and, frankly, a bit disappointing. Ouch!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don&#8217;t let this scenario become your reality. With Event Tickets Plus, you can take personalization to the next level by adding custom registration field info to each email.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Don&#8217;t just set it and forget it. Test different versions of your emails to see which ones get your attendees clicking and grinning. Tools like <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/promoter/\">Promoter</a> can help you track how well your emails are performing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-data-security\"><strong>Data security</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Data security is a top concern for event organizers, and with good reason. Imagine the fallout if your attendees&#8217; personal information or credit card details were compromised. It could lead to a loss of trust, damage to your reputation, and even legal consequences.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the world of events, your reputation is everything. Today, a data breach can spread like wildfire on social media, potentially impacting future event attendance and your overall business.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Event Tickets takes this seriously and uses trusted payment gateways like PayPal and Stripe to process payments. This means your attendees&#8217; financial information is protected by industry-standard encryption.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, the plugin is regularly updated to address any potential security vulnerabilities. By using Event Tickets, you&#8217;re doing more than just organizing an event; you&#8217;re giving your attendees peace of mind and showing them that you value their trust.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tips-for-promoting-events-and-driving-registrations\"><strong>Tips for promoting events and driving registrations</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You&#8217;ve set up your event registration page, but how do you get people to actually sign up? Here are some proven strategies to boost your event&#8217;s visibility and drive registrations:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Create a sense of urgency:</strong> Take a page from London&#8217;s <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/showcase/we-love-soul/\">We Love Soul</a> music venue. They use an Event Countdown widget right above their &#8220;Buy Tickets&#8221; link. This simple addition gets people excited and encourages them to register before time runs out.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Harness the power of social media:</strong> Create event pages on platforms like <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/\">LinkedIn</a>. Encourage your speakers and attendees to share the event on their profiles too. This expands your reach and taps into their networks.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Use email marketing:</strong> Build a targeted email list of potential attendees. Include past participants, industry contacts, and subscribers. Use tools like Promoter to automate your email campaigns and keep your community engaged.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Optimize for search engines: </strong>Make sure your event website is search-engine friendly. Use relevant keywords in your content, meta tags, and URLs. Create useful content related to your event topic to attract organic traffic.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Try paid advertising: </strong>Consider using Pay-Per-Click (PPC) advertising on promotional platforms. Target keywords related to your event and audience interests.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Offer incentives:</strong> Early bird discounts can create urgency and encourage early registrations. You could also offer referral incentives to attendees who invite friends or colleagues.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Of course, promoting your event is an ongoing process. Start early and use a mix of these strategies for the best results. With consistent effort, you&#8217;ll see those registration numbers grow!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-get-started-with-event-tickets-today\"><strong>Get started with Event Tickets today</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ve covered a lot of ground in this guide, from exploring top WordPress event registration plugins to diving deep into the features of Event Tickets. Now, it&#8217;s time to put this knowledge into action!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\">Event Tickets</a> stands out as a powerful, user-friendly solution for managing your event registrations. Here&#8217;s why it&#8217;s a great choice:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>It’s easy to use. You don&#8217;t need to be a tech expert to set up tickets for your events.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It’s <em>packed</em> with features. From ticket sales to attendee management, it&#8217;s got you covered.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It works perfectly with WordPress.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It handles ticketing for all types of events. Whether you&#8217;re planning an in-person conference or a virtual workshop, Event Tickets is your best buddy.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The best part? You can get started with Event Tickets in just a few clicks. Installation is straightforward, and you&#8217;ll be up and running in no time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Successful events are just around the corner. Optimize your registration process with<a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-event-tickets/\"> Event Tickets</a> today!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/event-management/wordpress-event-registration/\">Your Go-To WordPress Event Registration Guide</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"Featured Calendar: Visit Franklin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:167:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/featured-calendar-visit-franklin/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 22 Aug 2024 18:30:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"WordPress Calendar Examples\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545582\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:620:\"<p>Each month, we have a blast digging into a website that uses The Events Calendar products. This time, we are showing you Visit Franklin (and they’ve wowed us with their site!) Their clean, earthy color scheme and seamless designs create a stunning, easy-to-navigate experience. Everything, from their graphics to their photos, fits together perfectly. We’re&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/featured-calendar-visit-franklin/\">Featured Calendar: Visit Franklin</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Sarah Zuercher\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19393:\"\n<p><br>Each month, we have a blast digging into a website that uses <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">The Events Calendar products</a>. This time, we are showing you <a href=\"https://visitfranklin.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Visit Franklin</a> (and they’ve wowed us with their site!) Their clean, earthy color scheme and seamless designs create a stunning, easy-to-navigate experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Everything, from their graphics to their photos, fits together perfectly. We’re especially impressed with their calendar, which is both beautiful and incredibly easy to navigate. It makes us eager to visit Franklin!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Join us as we dive into their website to uncover great tips for getting the most out of our products.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-homepage\">The homepage</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Upon reaching the homepage, you’ll be greeted by rolling footage of Franklin, Tennessee. The video at the top of the page captures Franklin’s undeniable charm through glimpses of buildings, activities, scenery, and food.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"256\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-665x256.png\" alt=\"A screenshot of the Visit Franklin homepage\" class=\"wp-image-2545593\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-665x256.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-300x116.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-140x54.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-768x296.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1536x591.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-430x166.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-645x248.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1068x411.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-460x177.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1074x413.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-512x197.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-707x272.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-600x231.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-500x193.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image.png 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>By looking at the homepage, you can see that the website is well built out. It has multiple call-to-action buttons, all centered around the theme of ensuring an incredible trip to Franklin. These buttons offer information on where to stay, whom to contact with questions, free guides on things to do, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Below you can see the two guides that they have on the homepage: Top 10 Things To Do in Franklin and the Summer 2024 Guide.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"218\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-665x218.png\" alt=\"Guides on a website\" class=\"wp-image-2545594\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-665x218.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-300x98.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-140x46.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-768x252.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-1536x504.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-430x141.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-645x212.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-1068x350.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-460x151.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-1074x352.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-512x168.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-707x232.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-600x197.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1-500x164.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-1.png 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We find these resources incredibly creative and valuable! They also serve as effective marketing tools. Guides like these are definitely worth considering for your own event planning!</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"aligncenter kt-sc2545582_042b66-54 wp-block-kadence-splitcontent\"><div class=\"kt-split-content-wrap kt-sc-media-side-left\" style=\"grid-template-columns:50% auto\"><div class=\"kt-sc-imgcol kt-sc-imgcol-bg-auto kt-sc-img-side-left\"><figure class=\"kt-split-content-media-image wp-image-container-2545601\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1416\" height=\"1782\" class=\"kt-split-content-img wp-image-2545601\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM.png 1416w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-238x300.png 238w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-665x837.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-68x85.png 68w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-768x967.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-1221x1536.png 1221w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-430x541.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-645x812.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-1068x1344.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-460x579.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-1074x1352.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-512x644.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-876x1102.png 876w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-421x530.png 421w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-1313x1653.png 1313w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-600x755.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.37 PM-500x629.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1416px) 100vw, 1416px\" /></figure></div><div class=\"kt-sc-textcol kt-sc-text-valign-center kt-sc-text-halign-center\"><div class=\"kt-sc-innter-col\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"922\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-665x922.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2545584\" style=\"width:304px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-665x922.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-216x300.png 216w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-61x85.png 61w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-768x1065.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-1108x1536.png 1108w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-430x596.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-645x894.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-1068x1481.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-460x638.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-1074x1489.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-512x710.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-795x1102.png 795w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-382x530.png 382w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-1192x1653.png 1192w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-577x800.png 577w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM-500x693.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-13-at-4.37.06 PM.png 1226w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>We also want to shout out this cool section! The layout is easy-to-read and the graphic is well-designed, serving as a compelling way to learn about the various parts of Williamson County.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"329\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-665x329.png\" alt=\"Discover Williamson County graphic\" class=\"wp-image-2545596\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-665x329.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-300x148.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-140x69.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-768x380.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-1536x759.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-430x213.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-645x319.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-1068x528.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-460x227.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-1074x531.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-512x253.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-707x350.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-600x297.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3-500x247.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-3.png 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-main-events-page\">The main events page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The main calendar page is located under “Things to Do” → “Events”. The blue and white layout is crisp and clean, and the title and description at the top of the page makes it clear that there are plenty of events to explore!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"321\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-665x321.png\" alt=\"Top page on a website\" class=\"wp-image-2545597\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-665x321.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-300x145.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-140x68.png 140w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-768x371.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-1536x741.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-430x207.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-645x311.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-1068x515.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-460x222.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-1074x518.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-512x247.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-707x341.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-600x290.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4-500x241.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-4.png 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you scroll down on the page, you come across a grid displaying all events. Use the arrows at the top left or on the bottom to view additional events. You also have the option to filter events by list, month, or day.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the left side, you’ll see <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-calendar-filter-bar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Filter Bar</a> in action! It categorizes events by category and by community, making it easier for users to find events that fit their needs. You can also search for events by using the search bar. We love it!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"665\" height=\"603\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-665x603.png\" alt=\"Events listed on a website\" class=\"wp-image-2545598\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-665x603.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-300x272.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-94x85.png 94w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-768x697.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-430x390.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-645x585.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-460x417.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-512x465.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-584x530.png 584w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-600x544.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5-500x454.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/image-5.png 1068w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-the-single-events-page\">The single events page</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>After clicking on an event, you’ll make it to the single events page. On the top, you’ll see the event title, location, dates, time, cost, and picture. There is also a “learn more” button that takes you to the event’s Facebook page!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1365\" height=\"2290\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716.png\" alt=\"Main calendar webpage of events\" class=\"wp-image-2545589\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716.png 1365w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-179x300.png 179w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-610x1024.png 610w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-51x85.png 51w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-768x1288.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-916x1536.png 916w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-1221x2048.png 1221w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-430x721.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-645x1082.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-1068x1792.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-460x772.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-1074x1802.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-512x859.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-657x1102.png 657w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-316x530.png 316w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-985x1653.png 985w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-477x800.png 477w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2024/08/Visit-Franklin-Single-Event-Page-e1724180909716-500x839.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1365px) 100vw, 1365px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The page then brings you to a description of the events with an option to add it to your calendar. Also, a map is embedded directly on the page! Each event page also includes recommendations for other events, offering users more options and ideas.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We also need to point out their beautiful footer on every page! Users can sign up to keep connected. The simplicity and beauty of this call-to-action is unmatched. Plus, it helps build a robust email list for sharing future events.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-we-think-this-calendar-has-it-all\">We think this calendar has it all.</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Visit Franklin’s website is a prime example of how to use <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Events Calendar Pro</a> and <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-calendar-filter-bar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Filter Bar</a>. Additionally, their use of colors, graphics, and images provides great inspiration for creating a visually appealing website!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Start a <a href=\"https://demo.theeventscalendar.com/request-demo-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">free demo site</a> to begin visualizing your new event website! And <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">get help</a> if you have any questions along the way.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/wordpress-calendar-examples/featured-calendar-visit-franklin/\">Featured Calendar: Visit Franklin</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"Event Tickets Plus 6.0.2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:159:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-plus/event-tickets-plus-6-0-2/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 20 Aug 2024 20:46:17 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Event Tickets Plus\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545573\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:583:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release Event Tickets Plus moves attendees, orders, and ticket-related endpoints registering for Power Automate and Zapier endpoints. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ⚙️ Tweaks Tweaked in this release: 🗣 Translations Updated language files and strings:</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-plus/event-tickets-plus-6-0-2/\">Event Tickets Plus 6.0.2</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2878:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-12 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">Event Tickets Plus moves attendees, orders, and ticket-related endpoints registering for Power Automate and Zapier endpoints.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-13 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Tweaked in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Moved attendee, orders, and ticket-related endpoint registering for Power Automate and Zapier endpoints to Event Tickets Plus.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added actions: `tec_tickets_plus_attendee_bind_implementations`</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-14 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files and strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>0 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>6 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/event-tickets-plus/event-tickets-plus-6-0-2/\">Event Tickets Plus 6.0.2</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"Events Calendar Pro 7.0.2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:161:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-7-0-2/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 20 Aug 2024 20:46:14 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Events Calendar Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2545575\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:567:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release This latest version of Events Calendar Pro added the Remove Event End Time from the Tweaks addon to the Photo, Summary, and Map views. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✨ Features New features in this release: ✅ Fixes Bugs&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-7-0-2/\">Events Calendar Pro 7.0.2</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Emily Negroni\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4667:\"\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-15 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">This latest version of Events Calendar Pro added the Remove Event End Time from the Tweaks addon to the Photo, Summary, and Map views.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-16 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-features\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2728.png\" alt=\"✨\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Features</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">New features in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Adding the Remove Event End Time feature from the Tweaks addon to the Photo, Summary, and Map views.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-17 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-fixes\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixes</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Resolves a pagination issue when using the `tec_events_pro_custom_tables_v1_series_event_view_slug` filter to override the default Series view. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Exporting all Attendees as a CSV file in the new Tickets Attendees Page. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Moved event-related endpoint registering for Power Automate and Zapier endpoints to Events Calendar Pro.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-18 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-tweaks\"> <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/2699.png\" alt=\"⚙\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Tweaks</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Tweaks in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added actions: `tec_events_pro_init` </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Changed views: `v2/map/event-cards/event-card/event/date-time`, `v2/photo/event/date-time`, `v2/summary/date-group/event/date/single`</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-19 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"h-translations\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f5e3.png\" alt=\"🗣\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Translations</h4>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Updated language files, strings:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>3 new strings added</li>\n\n\n\n<li>52 updated</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 fuzzied</li>\n\n\n\n<li>0 obsoleted.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-7-0-2/\">Events Calendar Pro 7.0.2</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:35:\"https://t